~ dot notation reaches into records and collections

#keeper: {
  name - Aldous Vane
  years at post - 31
  lamp lit - true
}

#findings: [
  { claim - Attention precedes perception, strength - strong }
  { claim - Looking is never neutral,       strength - moderate }
]

~ record field
@keeper.name served for @keeper.years_at_post years.

~ collection by index
The first finding was: @findings.0.claim

~ the renderer fuzzy-matches keys —
~ years at post and years_at_post and yearsAtPost
~ all resolve to the same value. the writer never has to remember
~ exact key formatting.

@keeper.years_at_post
@keeper.years at post
@keeper.yearsAtPost
